00:23:34.420 --> 00:23:40.990
you do in the microscope with a single cell.
You, pretty much, you combine transgenics

00:23:40.990 --> 00:23:49.160
with IVF. So, basically, you have the egg
and then you have the male reproductive cell

00:23:49.160 --> 00:23:55.471
inside the egg and it is in the male reproductive
cell, just one single cell, that you introduce

00:23:55.471 --> 00:24:01.982
the DNA. So, there is no rabbit there that
you introduce. I understand that for, if we're

00:24:01.982 --> 00:24:06.920
not familiar with the process, we might picture
something cruel that you take a bunny and

00:24:06.920 --> 00:24:09.690
you inject something to it, but it's not like
that at all. We work in the microscope with

00:24:09.690 --> 00:24:16.240
an individual cell and then you're bringing
into the world a healthy bunny. So, it's a

00:24:16.240 --> 00:24:23.970
very different process. And the other aspect
of this is that it is intrinsic to life that

00:24:23.970 --> 00:24:32.810
the life that comes into the world does so
by a process that is developed by a previous

00:24:32.810 --> 00:24:38.960
generation or by another living being. In
other words, no single life form in the world

00:24:38.960 --> 00:24:45.060
ever has the choice to come into the world.
It's always a decision, say, of our parents

00:24:45.060 --> 00:24:51.970
or if it's a non-human, it's a decision of
a human, so it is always, in this case there's

00:24:51.970 --> 00:24:58.750
no exception. The decision is always made
by others. The question here is bringing into

00:24:58.750 --> 00:25:04.880
the world a life form that did not exist before
and then we're back to the beginning of your

