00:31:47.740 --> 00:31:54.370
covers a wide range of types of art, including
biological experimentation, like we've just

00:31:54.370 --> 00:31:59.190
seen, robotic systems that behave like living
creatures, or computer simulation of life

00:31:59.190 --> 00:32:08.750
and that's what Couch Potato Farm is. It's
an electronic simulation of an ecosystem.

00:32:08.750 --> 00:32:12.820
So, I imagined what would life be like if
it could live in television signals, instead

00:32:12.820 --> 00:32:19.940
of living in the real world? And we have all
these different sources of electromagnetic

00:32:19.940 --> 00:32:25.730
radiation that surround us all the time. Increasingly,
we have Wi-Fi, television, radio, cellular

00:32:25.730 --> 00:32:32.730
telephones, we still don't really know the
effects that they have on real life, but this

00:32:32.730 --> 00:32:38.140
initial work now in capturing the energy from
television transmissions to power electronic

00:32:38.140 --> 00:32:45.250
devices. So, we do actually have now examples
of life that is powered by television signals.

00:32:45.250 --> 00:32:48.850
But I wondered what would happen if we could
actually have an ecosystem that lived within

00:32:48.850 --> 00:32:54.370
the television signals? So, I created Couch
Potato Farm that is a virtual ecosystem that

00:32:54.370 --> 00:32:59.890
watches television. So, it's a software system
into which I feed a television signal from

00:32:59.890 --> 00:33:06.950
a television tuner. So, this is an example
image from a television program and it lives

00:33:06.950 --> 00:33:13.460
off the television signal and you can see
its effects by it's, it changes the television

00:33:13.460 --> 00:33:16.880
signal. So, if we had a clean transmission
we'd see the image on the left, but after

00:33:16.880 --> 00:33:23.130
the ecosystem has extracted some of the energy
from that television signal, then we get an

00:33:23.130 --> 00:33:27.840
image, a distorted image on the right. And
you can see the work in the back corner of

00:33:27.840 --> 00:33:37.050
the lobby here running on a series of programs
just from live television. So, I wanted to

00:33:37.050 --> 00:33:43.320
explain a little bit about how the system
works. It takes in television signals from

00:33:43.320 --> 00:33:48.580
the TV tuner and then processes them through
two kinds of artificial life systems. One

00:33:48.580 --> 00:33:57.340
is a cellular automaton, which is similar
to Conway's Life. So, this is an earlier example

00:33:57.340 --> 00:34:04.530
of a computer program that, in some sense,
simulates life. It takes the state of one

00:34:04.530 --> 00:34:11.280
time, applies the series of rules, and then
generates a new state. And the basic domain

00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:20.530
of my Couch Potato Farm is a cellular automaton,
like this, that lives off the television signals.

00:34:20.530 --> 00:34:25.570
So, it takes in red, green and blue energies
in each pixel and now it has three layers

00:34:25.570 --> 00:34:33.669
instead of this single layer like Conway's
Life. And adjacent cells affect each other,

00:34:33.669 --> 00:34:38.639
but they're also affected by the external
signal. So, where we have a lot of blue, then

00:34:38.639 --> 00:34:43.950
we'll get very strong blue potatoes I call
them in this field because they watch television

00:34:43.950 --> 00:34:50.859
all the time. And that blue, if you have a
strong blue potato in a particular pixel,

00:34:50.859 --> 00:34:56.369
then it will tend to drain out the color from,
the blue color from the television signal.

00:34:56.369 --> 00:35:03.619
So, what you see in the affected television
has the blue color drained out. And so we

00:35:03.619 --> 00:35:13.319
have a time delay as we see one color, then
that gets drained out of subsequent images.

00:35:13.319 --> 00:35:19.320
Then I hypothesized another part of the ecosystem,
which were animals, which were mobile creatures

00:35:19.320 --> 00:35:26.170
that can move around within the ecosystem
and they would interact. They would feed off

00:35:26.170 --> 00:35:31.970
the potatoes as they moved around and interact
with each other. So, there are four species

00:35:31.970 --> 00:35:39.740
in this ecosystem. Particular animals eat
other animals of different species, or they

00:35:39.740 --> 00:35:45.880
mate with animals of the same species and
opposite gender. And they also affect the

00:35:45.880 --> 00:35:52.670
television signal in different ways to produce
an affected video.

00:35:52.670 --> 00:35:54.849
[pause]

