00:36:09.839 --> 00:36:16.920
And so, the animals are encoded with a genetic
algorithm. So, every time they mate, then

00:36:16.920 --> 00:36:23.260
they produce offspring with potential mutations
and a combination of the genes of the two

00:36:23.260 --> 00:36:29.000
parents. And the genes encode a variety of
factors, including the speed of the animals,

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:33.759
their longevity, the range at which they can
detect other animals of the same or different

00:36:33.759 --> 00:36:40.140
species. And so, as an ecosystem watches a
particular program, then you'll get a particular

00:36:40.140 --> 00:36:46.690
convergence on a solution that works for that
television program. And as the program changes,

00:36:46.690 --> 00:36:56.170
then you'll get a different population arising
that matches the characteristics the new program.

00:36:56.170 --> 00:37:03.690
So, when the animals mate, then they're, the
mother is static for awhile and then produces

00:37:03.690 --> 00:37:19.569
a new child which has the genes spliced from
the two parents with some possible mutation.

