00:46:44.339 --> 00:46:49.470
Spiny lobsters have been around for millions
of years; longer than humans. And they'll

00:46:49.470 --> 00:46:54.970
probably be around for millions of years after
we're gone. They're getting along just fine

00:46:54.970 --> 00:47:00.730
without us. And this is a draft of him projecting
effects onto the painting. We were playing

00:47:00.730 --> 00:47:09.420
around with having the projection bleed beyond
the edges of the canvas and make an animated

00:47:09.420 --> 00:47:15.920
border. So, meanwhile, I just happened to
be having a trip booked to visit my mother,

00:47:15.920 --> 00:47:22.069
who lives in Wisconsin. And she just happens
to live in a forest and this is a photo of

00:47:22.069 --> 00:47:29.130
her backyard. So, I spent a few days just
taking photos, sketching a lot of the plant

00:47:29.130 --> 00:47:34.079
life out there and then when I got back to
New York, I make made some compositional layouts

00:47:34.079 --> 00:47:41.170
just to get an idea. This is the first one.
I was inspired by all these really weird alien-looking

00:47:41.170 --> 00:47:46.549
fungus that were growing in the logs and tree
trunks in the forest. The second idea, I was

00:47:46.549 --> 00:47:53.430
thinking of a swampy future where we've created
so much global warming that we have these

00:47:53.430 --> 00:47:58.720
mutant Venus flytraps that you see at the
bottom of the screen, that are just eating

00:47:58.720 --> 00:48:04.900
up every protein source they can find in their
environment. And the third one, which is the

00:48:04.900 --> 00:48:09.390
one we all agreed was the most successful,
was also the most at keeping with Andrew's

00:48:09.390 --> 00:48:20.470
original idea of looking up through the leaves
in a forest. It's a mix of domestic and wild

00:48:20.470 --> 00:48:25.960
vegetation. This is the painting that was
created from it. You can see, for example,

00:48:25.960 --> 00:48:32.039
the chartreuse leaves at the bottom are inspired
from my mom's rhododendrons. Next to them,

00:48:32.039 --> 00:48:37.759
are leaves based on sketches of weeds I took
that were growing in the driveway. And some

00:48:37.759 --> 00:48:43.380
of them I took more liberty with like the
purple thistle things. I wanted to see what

00:48:43.380 --> 00:48:50.410
